subject: Redirection of  DONATE button in header of https://royalrehab.com.au
preview: Hi Martina, Indeed, the Donate button's URL on the tablet and mobile view is still the old link. I'm sorry about that. Rest assured, I have updated the links to both tablet and mobile views.Please do

full_threads.body:
Hi Martina, 

Indeed, the Donate button's URL on the tablet and mobile view is still the old link. I'm sorry about that. Rest assured, I have updated the links to both tablet and mobile views.

Please don't hesitate to reach out to us if you need further assistance.

Thanks very much Rica for redirecting the DONATE button in the header of https://royalrehab.com.au/ and for emailing me the video on how to change it myself in future.

Unfortunately the DONATE button in the header of https://royalrehab.com.au/, when viewed on a mobile, is still hyperlinking to the old link, royal-rehab.giveeasy.org, rather than where you kindly redirected the desktop DONATE btn to, https://donate.royalrehab.com.au/donate.

Today I have been experiencing problems with accessing https://royalrehab.com.au/ so I was dearly hoping you could make this change for me so that another donor doesn't inadvertently donate the old way.

Thank you very much in anticipation Rica.

MARTINA FOX​

Hi Martina, 

All is good, hope you are too. You can change the redirect of the Donate button, by editing the Homepage in Elementor then on the top of the editor click on "Edit Header". From there, you can change the redirect of the Donate button. I took the initiative to make the changes for you and I've also recorded a video on how I did it. 

See: https://share.getcloudapp.com/nOu5nPdb

Let us know if you would like further changes.
